    ],
    "lyrics": {
      "text": "What shall we now call you, O Saints of God? Ho-ly Cher-u-bim, for Christ doth rest up-on you at all times. Six-wing’d Ser-a-phim, in that__ ye glo-ri-fied Him with-out cease. Pure An---gels, for ye showed your bod-ies nought but scorn; and Pow---ers, for ye work through won-drous mir-a-cles. Your names are di--vers and man-i-fold, but great-er still are your gifts of grace. O in-ter--cede with the Sav-iour that our souls__ be__ saved."
    }
  }
}